    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Sure. We run with these params: `--metrics --pprof --pprofaddr=0.0.0.0`, and use a `go-expvar` datadog thingy configured like this:\r\n```\r\ninit_config:\r\n  \r\ninstances:\r\n  - expvar_url: \"http://127.0.0.1:6060/debug/metrics\"\r\n    namespace: \"geth\"\r\n    tags:\r\n      - \"client:geth\"\r\n    metrics:\r\n      - path: chain.*\r\n        type: counter\r\n      - path: trie.cachemiss\r\n      - path: trie.cacheunload\r\n      - path: txpool.*\r\n      - path: p2p.*\r\n      - path: les.*\r\n- path: eth.downloader.*\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou can take a peek at `http://127.0.0.1:6060/debug/metrics` with curl to see what stats you can choose from. ",
